You can unfollow folks on Facebook. Also, I flipped a coin and no longer have FB on my phone. Figured I only need one social media platform. Random factoid: Steve Jobs didn't let his kids use the tablet.

Tip: Switch to posting first thing in the morning instead of late at night. There are also apps like Offtime that let you temporarily block certain apps on your phone so you can be more productive or focus on other things (like family time.) Also, turn off Facebook and Instagram notifications on your phone so you don't constantly have stuff popping up.

@mrs.jennrogers You can "unfollow" friends to mute them from your feed without the social faux pas of unfriending them! I was doing that for a while to minimize my news feed. I was always concerned about missing things on social media (after turning off notifications) and that was my primary drive to log in. After I let go of that sense of urgency, I ended up suspending my Facebook account and don't really miss it. Instagram and twitter are enough! Working on checking these accounts less and maintaining focus.

I started my blog and YouTube channel during highschool and I was steadily uploading for two years and then was uploading on and off for about another 2, 3 years and eventually j just stopped uploading. I was also very excited everytime my subscriber count or views went up but somewhere along the way, I realized that I wasn't making content for myself anymore. I wasn't talking about beauty products because I wanted to share them. It became a chore. An assignment. And the views and subscribers that were growing at one point started to become a heavy weight on my shoulders. I also saw all the changes that social media was going through and how the Youtube that I loved was not the same anymore. That was when I lost my motivation to make videos. I started comparing my channel so heavily against others and it wasn't fun anymore. A lot of people have been encouraging me to start again, which I plan to, but with the right timing in my life. Life outside of Youtube has been very fulfilling as I've learned so much while being an observer. The motivation to start my channel and blog again is definitely growing after watching people like @mrs.jennrogers and you. People like you guys keep YouTube personal and real. And I think that's very important when using such a public platform.
